04577nam a22007815i 9783112209332DE-B159720230228020105.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831122093327 a10.1515/97831122093322doi  a(DE-B1597)566705  a(OCoLC)1197566246  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aHQ691.7 7aSOC0260002bisacsh1 aBentlage, Björn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut12aA Tale of Two Stories :bCustomary Marriage and Paternity. A Discourse Analysis of a Scandal in Egypt /cBjörn Bentlage. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (336 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aIslamkundliche Untersuchungen ,x0939-1940 ;v33300tFrontmatter -- tTable of contents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tPrologue -- tChapter One: Special Discourse - The Legal Story of Hind and Aḥmad -- tChapter Two: Interdiscourse - The Public Story of Aḥmad and Hind -- tChapter Three: Discourse Analysis - Perspectives on Legal Change and Development -- tConclusion -- tBibliography0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book inves­ti­gates an Egyp­tian scandal about paternity and marriage in the years 2004 to 2007. It asks about legal change in Egyp­tian family law and Islamic juri­s­pru­dence while also inqui­ring into the effects of media coverage. The study draws from a variety of sources, inclu­ding news­paper arti­cles, court rulings, univer­sity text­books, fatwas, etc. The resul­ting presen­ta­tion tells two diffe­ring stories about the affair of Hind al-Ḥinnāwī and Aḥmad al-Fīšāwī: one is dramatic and promises change, the other is tech­nical and purports routine. In order to make sense of this, both stories are situated in a discourse analytical frame­work. Buil­ding on the distinc­tion of special discourse, inter­dis­course, and elemen­tary discourse, the combined analysis of both tales deve­lops a new perspec­tive on the issue of change and arrives at an inter­dis­cur­sive view of legal deve­lop­ment in Egyp­tian family law.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW0 cprintz978387997464140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311220933240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783112209332423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783112209332/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020